			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There are many, many ways to do it.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Probably the simplest way is with Blending Options.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Put whatever it is you want to make glow on it's own layer and then right-click on the layer and go to Blending Options -&gt; Outer Glow.  Tinker with the various options given until you like the result.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
You can also do some interesting effects by duplicating the layer, then blurring the underlying layer to create the glow.  It will be very subtle at first, so duplicate the blurred layer to intensify the glow.  Once you've got it where you like it, merge all the blurred layers together.  This technique has the advantage that the glow will alter color based on the original object's colors.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
There are other ways to make a glow, but those two should be sufficient for most of your needs. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
