				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">New info on chrome effects (any many other nifty effects).  Without buying expensive filters.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
The Layer Blending Options in Photoshop 6 or 7 are absolutely amazing.  I recently discovered how incredibly versatile they are.  You can achieve a wide array of effects (chrome being just one) with simple Layer Blending settings.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
I strongly suggest anyone who's making sigs with Photoshop to go out and buy (or get from your library, which is what I did) &quot;The Photoshop 6 WOW! Book&quot; from Peachpit Press.  Not only is it a great tutorial on the basics of Photoshop, it also has a companion CD with hundreds of pre-made Layer Effects that you can add to your text or other shapes with a single click.  20+ different types of chrome/steel effects alone!
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Making this thread sticky... 
