			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">...going back to the "glow" effect if anyone is still interested....
<br />

<br />
Make a new layer, take a medium round brush, 0 hardness, 100% opacity and draw with white or whatever glow color you want around the object you want to "glow". Use Gaussian Blur, repeat as needed.  Thats a really simple way, but there are other ways as well.
<br />

<br />
If you want to make something you drew glow (spell effects, see sig) or text, you can use PS7's layer style "outer glow"  Just make sure whatever spell effects you draw in are done using WHITE PAINT.  It doesn't matter what color you want your effects, use WHITE.  When you set the layer to "outer glow" then you can set the color of the glow to whatever you want, and it gives the effect like they are glowing...see sig...white paint, blue glow.
<br />

<br />
Anyway...just trying to help <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
As for chrome, on text I use one of my many many styles, in the styles palette.  Or Eye Candy 4000.  But I don't use much chrome except for text lately.
<br />

<br />
Sveva<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://cosmosue.net/Sigs/SigforBLboards.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
